2. Loop through each entry in the original dictionary (`original_dict`).
3. Check if the current value of `original_dict` matches the desired condition (`value >= n`). If it does, add the corresponding key-value pair (index, value) to `filter_dict`.
4. Finally, check if the `filter_dict` contains any keys (`!in`) that correspond to the desired conditions (`{!in}!{!in}`). If so, return `true` as the result indicating that the filter was successful.
